1
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,160
This is our dream.

2
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:37,840
We've dreamed for a long time
of working with Darathong Music.

3
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:40,120
You'll be the one handling business calls

4
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:42,880
or anyone else who calls.
You can do that, right?

5
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,880
You won first place
in the singing contest.

6
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:48,720
Why are you here hanging laundry?

7
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:52,560
PREVIOUS EPISODE

8
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:54,240
Are you crying?

9
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,040
Chang, let's go!

10
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,440
Mr. Sonrak, don't go!

11
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,360
It's my fault.

12
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:06,000
If I hadn't run,
I wouldn't be in this mess.

13
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:12,800
What are you doing?

14
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:15,120
-Calling the police.
-No need!

15
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,320
But someone's dead.

16
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,400
-Yak.
-Yes?

17
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:21,360
-Take care of it.
-Got it, Boss.

18
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:29,800
Where are you taking the body?

19
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:31,240
None of your business.

20
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,320
Hey, if you want to work for us,

21
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:38,520
keep your mouth shut. Don't talk too much.

22
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,640
-Yes.
-Yes.

23
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:43,480
Get Sonrak to the event already.
Are you okay?

24
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,560
I'm fine, Dad.

25
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:48,640
Let's go, Boss.

26
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:11,240
Get more people
to help secure the company.

27
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:13,680
The security guards alone

28
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,600
won't be enough.

29
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,200
Sure.

30
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:21,920
I'll tell Chart to send more men.

31
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:27,040
Then I'll use Puna's promo budget.

32
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:31,840
Take care of Boss Noo for me.

33
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:33,800
Got it, buddy.

34
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,400
If there's money,

35
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:38,600
I'll take care of Boss Noo right away.

36
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,000
What happened, Khod?

37
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:05,760
I failed, Boss. Singha managed to escape.

38
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:10,840
Hod, the one you sent for Sonrak,

39
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,640
has been taken out, Boss.

40
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,480
You messed up!

41
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,680
Sorry, Pleaw.

42
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:00,840
Today, you have
a YouTube interview scheduled.

43
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:02,680
I've booked three hours for it.

44
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,400
After that, you'll be doing
a product review

45
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:06,280
for Mae Tuk Gold Shop until the evening.

46
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,040
Given the situation,
someone should stay with the car.

47
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:13,000
If someone attacks again,
it'll be a problem.

48
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,880
Then you two stay with the car.

49
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,440
Leave Mr. Sonrak to me inside.

50
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:20,120
Let's go.

51
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:24,880
Hey.

52
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:29,000
I don't think Sonrak knows anything
about his father's business.

53
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:34,400
Singha probably hides the dark side,

54
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:36,320
creating a good image
to deceive his own son.

55
00:06:58,640 --> 00:06:59,920
Sorry, Boss,

56
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,080
for my men's mistake.

57
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:07,880
This time, luck was on their side.

58
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:13,960
But next time, make sure we get them.

59
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,480
Yes, Boss.

60
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:18,040
And don't forget to send our men
to his music label.

61
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,880
What do you want us to do?

62
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:23,120
Burn it all down.
Make sure it's completely destroyed.

63
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,080
Got it, Boss.

64
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:12,760
Pleaw!

65
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:21,600
This is the rest.

66
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,560
And the tip from my boss.

67
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:28,600
For just injuring Sonrak,
we still get this big of a tip?

68
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,640
I like it. Hey, Jan.

69
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,919
Take this and count it.

70
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,360
Zip it, you guys.

71
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:40,559
Unless it's necessary,
don't show yourselves.

72
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,440
Got it, bro.

73
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,920
-Awesome.
-Remember this.

74
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:53,200
I'm ready to send all of you

75
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:54,920
to the afterlife.

76
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:03,320
DARATHONG MUSIC

77
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:16,360
-She should know the schedule.
-I'll handle it.

78
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,280
Excuse me.

79
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:24,200
Oh my, you're looking so glowy today!

80
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:25,440
What did you do to your face?

81
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:28,440
Really? My face looks that good?

82
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:31,960
Absolutely! Your skin is glowing.
It's like you have an aurora.

83
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:34,600
-Aura.
-Yes, aura!

84
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:36,080
Yeah.

85
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:38,720
I didn't do anything.
Maybe it's just natural.

86
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,200
Oh, really?

87
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:45,080
By the way, do you know
Mr. Sonrak's schedule today?

88
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,160
Where is he going, and what's he doing?

89
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,960
No one knows the schedule,

90
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:51,640
except his assistant.

91
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:54,400
There he is, coming now.

92
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:56,120
Besides the assistant, no one else knows?

93
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:58,320
No one knows.

94
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:01,680
If anyone did and it leaked to the fans,
it'd be chaos.

95
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:04,280
Hello.

96
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:06,280
-Excuse me.
-Of course.

97
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:10,280
My skin looks that good?
I didn't do anything.

98
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:12,000
Mr. Manat!

99
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:19,520
Mr. Manat.

100
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:24,200
Do you know Mr. Sonrak's schedule today?
Where's he going, and what's he up to?

101
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,960
Tell Miss Maria to agree
to my offer first,

102
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,080
then I'll take care of it.

103
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,720
He says

104
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,000
you need to agree to his offer first.

105
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,920
You know what the offer is, right?

106
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:06,360
If you can take down
the one who helped Sonrak,

107
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:07,960
I'll give you more money.

108
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:15,520
The money maker is right in front of us.

109
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:17,720
You guys go take care of it.

110
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,440
Got it. Should we kill him?

111
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:25,040
Killing him would be even better.
I'll pay more.

112
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,320
Let's run!

113
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,400
Hey! Go tell your boss

114
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:03,280
he should put on a skirt!

115
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:19,240
It's a shame the superintendent
didn't approve the search warrant.

116
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:22,200
We could have gotten some clues.

117
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:26,280
One day, fate will intervene.

118
00:12:27,040 --> 00:12:27,880
Just be patient.

119
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:33,040
Let's check inside.
Maybe we'll find something useful.

120
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,040
-Let's go.
-Yes, sir.

121
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,960
Three, two, one.

122
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,960
Hey, he's running off! Follow him!

123
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,440
Split up.

124
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,120
Where are you going?

125
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,320
Sounds like a fight, Captain.

126
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:08,840
Let's go check!

127
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,920
Who sent you to hurt Mr. Sonrak that day?

128
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,440
Didn't you hear me?

129
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:21,360
Answer me!

130
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:24,480
Boss Noo sent me.

131
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:25,920
Boss Noo?

132
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,440
What's the deal between them?

133
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:35,520
Why would he send you to hurt Sonrak?

134
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:38,360
I don't know!
I just took the job from him.

135
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,960
I don't know what their issue is.

136
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,880
Hey! What's going on here?

137
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:48,560
Help me! I'm being bullied!

138
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:49,920
Stop! Hands up!

139
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:52,560
Now!

140
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:55,320
Get up!

141
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:57,400
Quick!

142
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:03,440
Come on, Sergeant.

143
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:06,560
Kneel.

144
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,560
Kneel!

145
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:10,720
Kneel now!

146
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:19,360
Sergeant.

147
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:21,080
Get them.

148
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:28,760
Hold on, Sergeant!

149
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,480
-Ouch!
-Don't move!

150
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,160
-Don't struggle.
-It hurts, Sergeant.

151
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:34,000
Sergeant.

152
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,160
Take it easy.

153
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:42,600
-Sergeant, take them in for questioning.
-Roger.

154
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,880
What about this picture?
Is there something wrong?

155
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:04,680
What's your relationship with Sonrak?

156
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,280
Earlier,

157
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:12,440
Mr. Sonrak was attacked.
We went to help him.

158
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,400
Now we're working as his bodyguards.
That's it, Captain.

159
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:20,160
Yes, he hired us to ensure his safety.

160
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:23,560
I see. Good citizens, huh?

161
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:27,560
The one who attacked Sonrak
is the thug from earlier.

162
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:31,880
Yes, go catch him. Let us go now.

163
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:34,320
Captain, I think…

164
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,320
Aside from being bodyguards,

165
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:38,360
do you know anything else
about what they're up to?

166
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,480
What are you talking about? I don't know.

167
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:43,200
I don't believe you.

168
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:47,640
We really don't know.
We don't know what else to say.

169
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:50,200
Chaiya. Manat.

170
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:54,760
Captain, what did they do wrong?
What's going on here?

171
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,760
-Nothing.
-Nothing?

172
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,240
Then move!

173
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:03,320
If they haven't done anything wrong,
let them go! Why detain them?

174
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:06,640
-Are you going to harass the citizens?
-Calm down, ma'am.

175
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:08,720
I can't stay calm!

176
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:12,240
I can't stand seeing people
being mistreated,

177
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,319
especially these two handsome guys.

178
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,880
You're not hurt, are you?

179
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,680
Did they harm you anywhere?

180
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:21,520
If they do anything to you, tell me.

181
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:23,800
I'm a great whistleblower.

182
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,319
I'll make sure the world knows!
Everyone will know!

183
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:29,920
I'll post it all over social media,
recording a video! Look at this.

184
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,320
This officer is harassing
the innocent citizens.

185
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:35,160
They didn't do anything wrong.
He wants to make a name for himself,

186
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:37,040
-arresting people randomly.
-Hold on.

187
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:39,120
Calm down, ma'am.

188
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,680
-We're fine.
-Thank you so much, ma'am.

189
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,120
-Are you sure?
-Yes.

190
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,320
-They didn't threaten you, right?
-No.

191
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,920
Let's go, Sergeant!

192
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,200
Oh, raising your voice now?

193
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:59,680
Aren't you following your boss?
What are you waiting for?

194
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:01,720
Just admiring the beautiful woman.

195
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:07,520
Stop always telling the truth!
Complimenting me again, it's so boring.

196
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:08,800
Can't I compliment you?

197
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:10,760
Just go, quickly.

198
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:14,680
Thank you so much, ma'am.

199
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,880
If it weren't for you, we'd be in trouble.

200
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:20,640
-Can you thank me in another way?
-You're so kind, ma'am.

201
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:23,560
You must've been very beautiful
when you were young.

202
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:27,120
Oh my goodness, you have good eyes.

203
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,400
Honestly,

204
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:31,440
when I was younger,
scouts were chasing after me.

205
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:34,560
They wanted to get me into the industry,
to act in dramas.

206
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:36,760
But I didn't want to do it.

207
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,320
True story.

208
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:42,800
Oh my goodness.

209
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,760
Are you proposing, Chaiya?

210
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:49,400
Oh yes, anytime, anywhere, I'm ready!

211
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,920
Put a ring on it!

212
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:55,320
How many kids should we have? Twins?

213
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:57,640
How about five kids?

214
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,960
Both boys and girls!

215
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:01,200
-Ma'am.
-I'm all flustered now. What?

216
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:03,800
I know! Put it on already!

217
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,000
My shoelace is undone.

218
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:13,720
Is it too late to pull my hand back?

219
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:16,320
What a timing.

220
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:18,920
Let's go.

221
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:22,600
We'll leave now. Thanks again, ma'am.

222
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:24,960
Goodbye. Let's go.

223
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:33,400
What was I thinking? What did I just do?

224
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:35,840
Oh well, luckily I'm beautiful.

225
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:39,080
He probably thinks
the clumsy girl is adorable.

226
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:43,200
This type of woman is what men like.
Wait for me!

227
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:47,960
Earlier today, Captain Tom

228
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:50,560
wanted to check the warehouse
for any remaining evidence,

229
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,520
so I took him inside.

230
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:55,320
Did you find
anything interesting, Sergeant?

231
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,480
Found a bit of chemical residue.

232
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:01,640
It's the chemicals
they left at the company.

233
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:07,200
Anyway, we'll try to gather
more infomation at the company.

234
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:10,480
Good idea. Help the captain out.

235
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:12,280
I feel bad for him.

236
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,640
His boss is always giving him a hard time.

237
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:17,680
I've already filed a complaint
against Superintendent Samuejai.

238
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,400
Tell him to hang in there.

239
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:21,440
Thanks.

240
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:31,160
CHALOE COFFEE AND BAR

241
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,280
Just coffee doesn't count.

242
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:38,040
That's not part of the deal.

243
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:44,840
Who said there's no food here?

244
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:49,760
-Sophie, Joey.
-Here you go!

245
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:55,600
Hot garlic chicken rice is here!

246
00:20:56,320 --> 00:20:57,720
-Takeout rice?
-Yes.

247
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,920
You said I'd have one meal with you.

248
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:03,840
Here's one for you too,
Miss Maria. There it is.

249
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,600
Enjoy. This place makes really tasty food.

250
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:09,800
That's right.

251
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:18,080
I've eaten. Done.

252
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:19,960
Just one bite?

253
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:21,880
You didn't say I had to eat more.

254
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:24,400
What is this? You're eating just one bite?

255
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:25,800
The atmosphere isn't even right.

256
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:29,080
Are you here to eat
or to enjoy the atmosphere?

257
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:32,440
Go ahead. Eat! It'll get cold!

258
00:21:36,440 --> 00:21:37,520
What?

259
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,240
Mr. Sonrak's schedule.

260
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,720
-Which day?
-Today.

261
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,320
Mr. Sonrak has a live session
at the company.

262
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:47,320
-Is that it?
-That's it.

263
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:50,040
We can't schedule anything outside
because we're worried about attacks.

264
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:52,240
-What about tomorrow?
-One meal, one day.

265
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:57,240
You said you wanted to know
what Mr. Sonrak does every day.

266
00:21:57,320 --> 00:21:59,720
If you want to know more,
come eat with me again.

267
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:04,840
Delicious.

268
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:08,240
Eating near a beautiful lady

269
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,200
makes it even better.

270
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:16,160
I forgot I have something to do.
Sophie, Joey, let's go.

271
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:21,080
We'll leave first. Bye.

272
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,920
-Hello.
-Goodbye!

273
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,480
DARATHONG MUSIC

274
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:42,520
Hey, Chaiya.

275
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:44,880
Is it almost time?

276
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:47,360
Half an hour left.

277
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:50,200
-Are you done?
-All set.

278
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:54,440
Then it's time to check the company
for clues for Captain Tom.

279
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:58,960
I'll stop the security cameras first,
then we'll split up.

280
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:02,280
You check the accounting room,
and I'll check Mr. Singha's office.

281
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:06,440
If you find anything interesting,
take pictures.

282
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,480
We'll analyze them later.

283
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:11,120
-Got it. That's the plan.
-Let's go.

284
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:33,600
CONTROL ROOM

285
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:05,880
PURCHASE AND SALES DOCUMENTS

286
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:28,520
Where did all the employees go?

287
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:31,160
The livestream team is probably inside.

288
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:34,120
-Then lead the way.
-Let's go.

289
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,560
Alright, let's go.

290
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:42,160
What's up, Manat?

291
00:24:42,760 --> 00:24:44,200
-Someone's here.
-Abort the mission.

292
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:52,440
CONTROL ROOM

293
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:09,720
Mr. Assistant.

294
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,600
Has Mr. Sonrak arrived yet?

295
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:15,720
Not yet, but he's on his way.

296
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:16,840
Is that so?

297
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:27,240
Miss Maria, let's go to the dressing room.

298
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:28,240
Excuse us.

299
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:36,040
-Hey! Hey.
-What?

300
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:39,040
There's no schedule
for Miss Maria today, right?

301
00:25:40,120 --> 00:25:42,440
A sudden schedule.
Get ready. They're pairing up.

302
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:46,760
-Did you find any evidence?
-Nothing at all. What about you?

303
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:48,280
I've already taken some photos.

304
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:51,240
Okay. I'll be back in a bit.

305
00:25:51,320 --> 00:25:52,640
Where are you going now?

306
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:55,680
Just checking something around here.

307
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:58,000
-Be right back.
-Alright.

308
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:03,360
You're fast with things like this.

309
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:08,480
MARIA DARATHONG

310
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:10,000
I knew you'd come.

311
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:14,840
Yeah, thanks for telling me.

312
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:18,120
Where are we eating tomorrow?
Same place, okay?

313
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:21,920
No, you don't need to come.

314
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:24,560
Don't you want to know the schedule?

315
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:31,000
Come on. If you come tomorrow,
I'll give you two days' worth.

316
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,880
-Really?
-Of course.

317
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:38,000
Let's exchange contacts.

318
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:42,240
What's this? Are you trying
to get my contact info?

319
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:44,480
If you don't want to, that's fine.

320
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:47,520
But if we miss each other,
I can't help that.

321
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:51,600
Fine. Give me your phone.

322
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:07,720
Hey, hold out your hand.

323
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:19,960
An amulet?

324
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:23,040
Venerable Father Dang
from Sanandong Temple.

325
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:27,720
Since you're becoming a famous singer,

326
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:29,680
you should wear
something with good fortune.

327
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:34,000
I want you to succeed.

328
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:37,520
I hope you achieve the fame you deserve,
Maria Darathong.

329
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:56,720
I'm going now.

330
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,480
The thug named Weerachai

331
00:28:15,560 --> 00:28:18,080
was caught by Sonrak's bodyguards, Boss.

332
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:21,480
Did he say anything about me?

333
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:23,960
I sent Khod to capture him
for questioning.

334
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,920
He said he didn't say anything.

335
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:30,400
You believe him?

336
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:37,400
Boss, please don't hurt me.
I didn't do anything!

337
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:42,280
Are you sure?

338
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:44,600
I swear, Boss.

339
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:48,200
I didn't say anything. I swear.
They don't know anything.

340
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:56,160
Alright.

341
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,240
I believe you.

342
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:02,920
-Take him away.
-Yes, sir.

343
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:08,600
-Pleaw, finish him.
-Yes, Boss.

344
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:10,360
Boss!

345
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:13,640
Please don't kill me! I beg you.

346
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:18,840
Please don't kill me.
Have some mercy on me.

347
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:21,000
I'll do anything.

348
00:29:21,080 --> 00:29:23,560
Really, I'll do anything.

349
00:29:29,680 --> 00:29:30,800
You'll do anything?

350
00:29:32,120 --> 00:29:33,640
Anything, Boss.

351
00:29:35,760 --> 00:29:36,600
Anything?

352
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:40,080
I'll do anything.

353
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:45,840
Good.

354
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:53,000
DARATHONG MUSIC

355
00:29:57,520 --> 00:29:59,560
Is there anything I can help with?

356
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:01,760
Sure you can help?

357
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:06,760
If it's about ironing the shirt,
no problem.

358
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:09,360
Here. Let me help.

359
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:28,480
You're good at this.
The shirt is perfectly neat.

360
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:31,440
I told you, I've done this before.

361
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:35,920
Hey, I have a question for you.

362
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:40,120
That day, when they
were giving out donations,

363
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:41,840
what did you do around the restroom?

364
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:51,040
Nothing. I wasn't doing anything.

365
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:54,120
But I saw you spying
on people entering the bathroom.

366
00:30:57,720 --> 00:31:00,360
Are you a pervert or something?

367
00:31:05,840 --> 00:31:08,720
You're definitely a pervert.

368
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:11,640
Don't come any closer.

369
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:14,720
Stop!

370
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:17,480
-Stop!
-Are you crazy?

371
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:20,320
What makes you think that?
What's up with you?

372
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:24,080
Then explain it.

373
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:27,040
Why were you secretly watching people
go into the restroom?

374
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:33,640
I saw a suspicious person,
so I followed them.

375
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:36,720
Then you saw me
when the bad guys threw a grenade.

376
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:38,480
Do you remember?

377
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:41,120
Hey! What are you doing here?

378
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:43,440
What about you? What are you spying on?

379
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:56,800
So you were spying on the bad guys.

380
00:31:59,600 --> 00:32:03,640
Now that I think about it,
you do kind of look like a cop.

381
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:08,360
With a face like this, I look like a cop?

382
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:11,240
If I were a cop, I'd arrest you first.

383
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,080
On what charge?

384
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,240
Stealing hearts.

385
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:25,640
Do you even realize

386
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:27,840
how cute you are?

387
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:42,360
I can't stand you anymore.

388
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:45,480
I put on powder. I smell good.
Take a sniff.

389
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:50,120
-Go away. You stink!
-I smell good.

390
00:32:58,720 --> 00:33:01,080
You can leave now.
Mr. Sonrak's coming soon.

391
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:03,120
I've still got so much to do.

392
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:11,600
Puna.

393
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,560
Is Mr. Sonrak's outfit almost ready?

394
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,680
The live stream's about to start.

395
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:16,960
It's ready.

396
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:20,680
Do you want to change now?
I can take it to the changing room.

397
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:22,520
No need to take it there.

398
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:24,920
I'll change here.

399
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:47,320
Hey, this is your boss's personal matter.

400
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:49,600
Stay still.

401
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:54,560
Please don't do this to Puna.

402
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:56,200
She's still young.

403
00:33:58,680 --> 00:33:59,880
But you smell so good.

404
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:03,880
Sorry, Mr. Sonrak,

405
00:34:03,960 --> 00:34:07,040
but I don't like this kind of thing.

406
00:34:12,679 --> 00:34:15,840
I was just joking around.
Don't take it seriously.

407
00:34:19,560 --> 00:34:22,280
I'll help you put it on, Mr. Sonrak.

408
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:23,480
It's time now.

409
00:34:33,199 --> 00:34:36,400
Something seems off,
like it's missing something.

410
00:34:37,159 --> 00:34:42,239
This outfit is supposed
to have a brooch attached.

411
00:34:42,320 --> 00:34:43,159
Really?

412
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:52,600
I'll attach it for you too.

413
00:34:52,679 --> 00:34:53,760
Move.

414
00:34:55,239 --> 00:34:56,120
It'll be quicker this way.

415
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:57,680
Hey.

416
00:34:58,200 --> 00:34:59,280
That's Puna's job.

417
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:01,440
Hand it over here.

418
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:02,920
-Wait a minute.
-Give it to me!

419
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,120
Hold on.

420
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:09,000
Puna, what are you doing?

421
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:12,240
Why aren't you being careful?
Mr. Sonrak is hurt.

422
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:17,280
Calm down. It's not Puna. It's Chaiya.

423
00:35:19,640 --> 00:35:22,280
Mr. Sonrak, I'm sorry.

424
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:27,360
It's okay, forget it.
If you have something to do, go ahead.

425
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:29,000
Yes.

426
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:39,920
Oh no!

427
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:41,120
There's blood!

428
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:43,200
Oh my, he's really bleeding!

429
00:35:44,480 --> 00:35:47,080
Quickly, take off your shirt.
I'll treat the wound.

430
00:35:47,160 --> 00:35:48,680
I'll take off the pants.

431
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,200
-Just the shirt, not the pants!
-Not there?

432
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:55,600
Puna, get the first aid kit!

433
00:35:56,720 --> 00:35:57,880
Hurry up, Puna!

434
00:35:57,960 --> 00:36:00,080
Stop standing there. Go quickly!

435
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,680
I'm so worried.

436
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:03,880
Quickly!

437
00:36:03,960 --> 00:36:04,880
Now!

438
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,480
DRESSING ROOM

439
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:11,840
Puna, wait here.

440
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,800
I'll go get the first aid kit.

441
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:14,720
Okay.

442
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:25,320
Thanks so much for helping me earlier.

443
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:30,000
I just don't like how he treated you.

444
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:34,200
I don't like it either.

445
00:36:42,040 --> 00:36:43,360
Next time,

446
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:45,920
if you need help,

447
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:48,280
just let me know.

448
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:50,360
I'll find a way to help.

449
00:36:58,320 --> 00:36:59,760
Thanks.

450
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:11,000
Here's the first aid kit.

451
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:16,480
Did you get the first aid kit?

452
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:20,800
-Here it is.
-Let Puna carry it inside.

453
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:22,760
-I'll help with that.
-No need.

454
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:25,920
Right now, the boss
can't stand the sight of you.

455
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:27,880
Stay away.

456
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:50,960
The first aid kit is here.

457
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:52,040
You finally--

458
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:54,360
Please hand it over.

459
00:38:02,400 --> 00:38:04,600
-Wait, Puna.
-Yes?

460
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:07,360
Take off my shirt for me.

461
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,320
I'll take it off for you.

462
00:38:12,240 --> 00:38:15,280
It's okay. This is Puna's job.

463
00:38:16,040 --> 00:38:17,440
She has to do it.

464
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:20,680
Hurry up. Don't keep him waiting.

465
00:38:31,520 --> 00:38:33,080
Be careful with the wound.

466
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:19,120
Can you do it?

467
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:22,840
-Yes, I can.
-Be careful not to touch the wound.

468
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:26,560
Ow.

469
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:27,920
Sorry.

470
00:39:29,440 --> 00:39:30,520
Slowly.

471
00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:44,720
What the heck is going on here?

472
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:08,560
<i>Don't let anyone hug these shoulders</i>

473
00:40:12,760 --> 00:40:18,440
<i>Don't let anyone grab these hands</i>

474
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:22,240
Teacher, why are you singing now?
Is this the right time?

475
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:31,120
<i>Don't let anyone kiss this forehead</i>

476
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:40,160
<i>Don't let anyone caress these cheeks</i>

477
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:42,680
Teacher, what song is this?

478
00:40:42,760 --> 00:40:43,880
Why?

479
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:46,240
The lyrics really move me.

480
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:48,720
-Teach me. I want to sing this song.
-Really?

481
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:51,480
Look at what he's doing.
It's really annoying.

482
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:53,480
Move aside.

483
00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:55,560
Finally done.

484
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:58,000
Put the shirt away.
Why are you standing here?

485
00:40:58,080 --> 00:40:59,120
Hurry up.

486
00:41:08,040 --> 00:41:09,480
Mr. Sonrak.

487
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:12,680
-Yes?
-Even though the wound is small,

488
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:14,440
it still needs to be treated.

489
00:41:15,040 --> 00:41:17,600
I used to be a Girl Scout.

490
00:41:18,400 --> 00:41:20,600
I was even the head of the nursing group.

491
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:23,760
Miss Maria, you're amazing!

492
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:26,400
If I'm not mistaken, you even won

493
00:41:26,480 --> 00:41:29,280
the First Aid Champion of Thailand.

494
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:31,240
That's impressive!

495
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:33,360
Really?

496
00:41:33,440 --> 00:41:36,120
Yes, even if the wound is small,

497
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:38,520
it could turn into something bigger.

498
00:41:38,600 --> 00:41:39,480
That's true.

499
00:41:40,200 --> 00:41:42,720
-Is it almost done?
-Almost.

500
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:45,320
It's finished.

501
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:48,360
She's really good at putting on bandages!

502
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:49,960
So what are you doing here?

503
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:54,960
I came to ask
if I could use the live studio

504
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:56,240
to promote my music.

505
00:41:57,240 --> 00:42:00,040
I didn't know today was your day.

506
00:42:00,640 --> 00:42:03,960
Could I please share my song

507
00:42:04,040 --> 00:42:06,760
and do a live stream on your channel?

508
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:07,920
It'll be quick.

509
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:10,120
No problem. If it's for work,
I'm happy to help.

510
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:14,920
Puna.

511
00:42:17,120 --> 00:42:18,360
Can you help with my outfit?

512
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:30,640
Then, I'll go change first.

513
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:32,320
Okay.

514
00:42:41,880 --> 00:42:45,480
It's annoying. He's with me,
but his eyes are always on Puna.

515
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:48,600
I can't stand it.
What's so special about her?

516
00:42:48,680 --> 00:42:49,640
Right.

517
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:53,640
Since we're at it,

518
00:42:53,720 --> 00:42:57,160
should we just completely ruin
her reputation today?

519
00:42:57,240 --> 00:42:58,840
Looks like her luck's running out.

520
00:42:59,560 --> 00:43:00,480
How?

521
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:03,040
We need to find a way to crush her.

522
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:05,840
Let me think for a second.

523
00:43:09,560 --> 00:43:11,040
How about this?

524
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:15,080
Miss Maria, you…

525
00:43:15,160 --> 00:43:17,120
Sophie, you…

526
00:43:25,320 --> 00:43:27,120
Are you thinking of using the bird?
The little chirp?

527
00:43:27,200 --> 00:43:28,680
Exactly, let's do it.

528
00:43:34,960 --> 00:43:36,760
-You've got this.
-Thank you.

529
00:43:39,680 --> 00:43:43,040
Please support Maria's new song.

530
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:46,160
I'll be releasing a new music video soon.

531
00:43:46,240 --> 00:43:48,480
Please stay tuned, everyone!

532
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:53,200
I think the fans would love to hear
you sing live during the stream.

533
00:43:54,600 --> 00:43:55,760
Sure!

534
00:43:56,560 --> 00:43:57,560
Please, go ahead.

535
00:43:58,760 --> 00:44:00,360
Music, please.

536
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:21,320
Go ahead, do it!

537
00:44:23,480 --> 00:44:24,600
Hurry before someone sees us!

538
00:44:26,400 --> 00:44:27,520
Exactly, like that!

539
00:44:37,760 --> 00:44:41,880
<i>Who owns this famous music label?</i>
<i>They say the boss</i>

540
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:44,400
<i>Is good looking</i>

541
00:45:06,640 --> 00:45:07,800
Hey, fire!

542
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:11,120
Fire! Help put it out!

543
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,600
Fire! Fire!

544
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:20,120
Fire?

545
00:45:22,200 --> 00:45:23,000
Hurry up!

546
00:45:23,080 --> 00:45:24,920
There's a fire!

547
00:45:26,480 --> 00:45:28,760
-Watch out!
-Fire!

548
00:45:59,120 --> 00:46:00,200
Fire!

549
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:03,800
-Get water, quick!
-Come on, everyone!

550
00:46:03,880 --> 00:46:06,160
Help put out the fire, fast!

551
00:46:06,240 --> 00:46:07,520
Fire!

552
00:46:07,600 --> 00:46:10,040
-Help with the fire.
-Fire!

553
00:46:10,120 --> 00:46:11,160
Move aside!

554
00:46:17,640 --> 00:46:20,200
-Puna, are you okay?
-I'm fine.

555
00:46:20,280 --> 00:46:22,600
Chaiya, get water
to help put out the fire.

556
00:46:24,200 --> 00:46:25,200
Yes.

557
00:46:30,480 --> 00:46:32,480
Miss Maria, are you okay?!

558
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:33,960
-I'm fine.
-Fire!

559
00:46:34,040 --> 00:46:35,760
What about Joey?

560
00:46:35,840 --> 00:46:38,040
-Haven't seen him yet.
-I'm here!

561
00:46:41,240 --> 00:46:43,480
-How is this happening?
-Why did the fire start?

562
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:45,440
-Go help put it out first.
-Yeah.

563
00:46:47,240 --> 00:46:48,360
How's it looking inside?

564
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:50,920
Move fast!

565
00:46:54,560 --> 00:46:55,640
I've called the fire truck.

566
00:46:56,680 --> 00:46:59,040
Everyone's helping to put out the fire,
doing what they can.

567
00:46:59,120 --> 00:47:02,760
Then hurry! Everyone, help! Come on!

568
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:05,440
-Quick, everyone!
-It's spreading everywhere.

569
00:47:14,000 --> 00:47:15,960
Everything went according to plan.

570
00:47:16,480 --> 00:47:19,240
You're not as dumb as you look.
Come here. I'll give you a kiss.

571
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:20,280
Hey!

572
00:47:20,360 --> 00:47:22,240
Even looking like this, I still pick.

573
00:47:23,080 --> 00:47:25,600
Let's go. Time to deal with Puna.

574
00:47:25,680 --> 00:47:27,520
-Sounds good.
-Stick to the plan.

575
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:28,680
Let's go!

576
00:47:31,400 --> 00:47:34,520
Jan, the job's done.
Let's get out of here.

577
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:35,960
Where are you rushing off to?

578
00:47:41,680 --> 00:47:42,960
Why do you care?

579
00:48:02,760 --> 00:48:05,080
-Who stole it?
-Puna.

580
00:48:06,320 --> 00:48:08,480
My company doesn't employ thieves.

581
00:48:09,800 --> 00:48:12,720
Pack your bag and go home. You're fired.

582
00:48:14,440 --> 00:48:18,160
I'll never let Puna outshine me.

583
00:48:18,240 --> 00:48:24,080
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

584
00:48:25,440 --> 00:48:27,840
Teacher, you know this song? Who sings it?

585
00:48:27,920 --> 00:48:31,320
NEXT EPISODE

586
00:48:32,120 --> 00:48:33,480
Are they waiting to trigger the bomb?

587
00:48:33,560 --> 00:48:35,240
Hey! Watch out!

588
00:48:36,640 --> 00:48:37,320
Stay back!

589
